MACROSCOPIC Three specimens received .
1 : The specimen is received fresh and is labelled  right lung " and consists of a right pneumonectomy specimen measuring 230 x 135 x 40 mm ."

Arising in the right lower bronchus , 17 mm from the bronchial resection margin , is an ulcerated friable cream tumour bulging into the bronchial lumen and - invading through the wall into the lung parenchyma .
The tumour measures 35 x 35 x 20 mm .
The bronchus distal to this lesion shows bronchiectasls .
The surrounding pleura shows multiple subpleural lymph nodes extending towards the inferior aspect of the lower lobe .
Sectioning the tumour mass shows multiple involved nodes in direct contact with the tumour .
Distal to the tumour there is also focal collapse with or without consolidation .
At the inferior ( diaphragmatic ) aspect of the lower lobe is an area of pleural thickening which appears unrelated to the tumour .
